FILE: A concert in honour of Mthokozisi Ntumba Braamfontein. (Sli_Masikane\eNCA\twitter) JOHANNESBURG - Four police officers accused of killing Mthokozisi Ntumba will be back in court on Monday. Ntumba was killed during student protests in Braamfontein 2021. READ: Mthokozisi Ntumba murder-accused granted bail They were arrested a few days after Ntumba, a bystander was shot dead on 10 March. The accused were dispersing a group of students who were protesting non-registration due to historical debt. They have been charged with murder and attempted murder and are out on bail of R8,000